"{\"content\":{\"body\":\"The (underrated) hoisin sauce is a thickened, fermented soy-sauce-like substance, flavored with chilies, garlic, vinegar, sugar, and, of course, exotic spices.Â It makes a great marinade. And unless you horribly overcook it, this skirt steak is juicy and tender.\\n\\n[ \\n ](https://www.allrecipes.com/cook/foodwisheswithchefjohn/)Step 1\\n\\nWhisk hoisin sauce, vinegar, soy sauce, hot sauce, sesame oil, grated ginger, garlic, brown sugar, salt, and pepper together in a large mixing bowl.\\n\\n* Step 2\\n\\n  Cut skirt steak crosswise into about 4 or 5 smaller pieces. Transfer steak into marinade and toss until all pieces are evenly coated. Cover with plastic wrap. Refrigerate; marinate at least 2 hours and up to 12 hours.\\n* Step 3\\n\\n  Line a baking pan with paper towels. Transfer pieces of steak to the paper towels and mop off some of the marinade.\",\"timestamp\":1638084736,\"title\":\"Grilled Hoisin Beef\"},\"digest\":\"RFTtFc2x1ZvVrWDtaluqgjGZ2CiN9OtzOlwMcTWCrAs\",\"authorship\":{\"contributor\":\"0xc11d801192DDD541Ac8D14b263f018f0836bD810\",\"signingKey\":\"{\\\"crv\\\":\\\"P-256\\\",\\\"ext\\\":true,\\\"key_ops\\\":[\\\"verify\\\"],\\\"kty\\\":\\\"EC\\\",\\\"x\\\":\\\"YeRtxtsySOzm4JIcLaEv_BgM0S-NRDHVRu8f7XGtPuk\\\",\\\"y\\\":\\\"NsruYhgdqHAjZD7qRfLgZZ0kb5tqEBInfSKbzyioHvM\\\"}\",\"signature\":\"UIvwmK6Z5q0Wx-IK4zhpLH5QSRlxeWYAxsK0D7TWwp0WFfvsMivdG-mm7pvuHoZBoXgZA-FItT8RzUok5zBsvA\",\"signingKeySignature\":\"0xccbb52a5c9040f53980e4406f2b6a66bf6461c4e41ef89319b821323f6e8282a41eb486aa2610aa7b0421121e0c8c6023e714befa1e4efb48d5b0efc99d54b601b\",\"signingKeyMessage\":\"I authorize publishing on mirror.xyz from this device using:\\n{\\\"crv\\\":\\\"P-256\\\",\\\"ext\\\":true,\\\"key_ops\\\":[\\\"verify\\\"],\\\"kty\\\":\\\"EC\\\",\\\"x\\\":\\\"YeRtxtsySOzm4JIcLaEv_BgM0S-NRDHVRu8f7XGtPuk\\\",\\\"y\\\":\\\"NsruYhgdqHAjZD7qRfLgZZ0kb5tqEBInfSKbzyioHvM\\\"}\",\"algorithm\":{\"name\":\"ECDSA\",\"hash\":\"SHA-256\"}},\"nft\":{},\"version\":\"12